# Project Rules for AI Agents

## Code Style

- Use TypeScript strictly; avoid `any` unless necessary
- Prefer functional components and hooks in React
- Use meaningful names; keep functions small and focused

## Naming

- Prefer **kebab-case** for file names (e.g. `use-raid-tracker.ts`, `raid-tracker-table/index.tsx`)
- Keep exported symbols idiomatic (e.g. `useRaidTracker` is fine), but keep **file paths** kebab-case
- Avoid oversimplified names for locals and callback params (e.g. `v`, `d`, `c`, `e`); prefer descriptive names like `event`, `nextValue`, `character`, `dungeon`

## Commit Messages

Use [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0/):

```
<type>[optional scope]: <description>
```

- **feat:** new feature (MINOR)
- **fix:** bug fix (PATCH)
- **docs:** documentation only
- **style:** formatting, no code change
- **refactor:** code change that neither fixes nor adds a feature
- **perf:** performance improvement
- **test:** adding or updating tests
- **chore:** build, CI, tooling
- **BREAKING CHANGE:** use `!` after type/scope or footer (MAJOR)

Example: `feat(auth): add login form`

## Versioning & Changelog

- Use [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/): MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH
- Version lives in `package.json`; shown in the app header via Vite `define` (`AppVersionLabel`)
- When releasing: bump `package.json` version, then add a `CHANGELOG.md` entry
- Changelog entries must describe **actual user-facing changes** included in the release (derived from commits/diff since the previous release), not just “bump version”

### Changelog format

- Follow [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/)
- File: `CHANGELOG.md` at project root
- Sections: `### Added`, `### Changed`, `### Deprecated`, `### Removed`, `### Fixed`, `### Security`
- Entry format: `## [X.Y.Z] - YYYY-MM-DD`
- Add new entries at the top (above previous releases)
- Do **not** add filler entries like “version bump for release”; if a release contains no notable changes, do not cut a release (or explicitly document why)

### Version bump rules

- **PATCH** — bug fixes, minor tweaks
- **MINOR** — new features, non-breaking changes
- **MAJOR** — breaking changes (use `BREAKING CHANGE` in commit)

## Editing

- Prefer editing existing files over creating new ones
- Preserve existing formatting and indentation
- Run linter after changes; fix any new issues

## Project Context

- React 19 + TypeScript + Vite app with Material UI (`@mui/material`, `@mui/icons-material`)
- WoW raid cooldown tracker: characters, dungeons, per-character–dungeon toggles
- Domain state in `useTrackerDomain` (alias `useRaidTracker`); persistence via `storage/index.ts` + `storage/parse.ts` / `storage/persist.ts` (`my-raid-cds` key, `schemaVersion` in saves; persisted snapshot type `PersistedTrackerState`; **current `schemaVersion` is 3**); dungeons list starts empty; corrupted saves reset with a load warning
- Main table UI: `components/raid-tracker-table/` (`RaidTrackerTable`); sort/search/delete UI state in `use-raid-tracker-table-state.ts`; shared confirm-before-delete in `hooks/use-pending-delete.ts`; toggle helpers in `utils/dungeon-toggles.ts`
- `data/raid-names.ts`, `data/class-specs.ts` (WotLK specs per class, `ClassSpecNames` with `en`/`ru`/`shortEn`/`shortRu`; duplicate spec names like Holy/Frost/Protection/Restoration differ per class), `data/dungeon-list.ts`, `create-template-dungeon.ts` — WotLK template raids (`RaidNames` metadata with `ru`/`en` names, `shortRu`/`shortEn` abbreviations, emblem + `DungeonList`; re-exported from `data/dungeons.ts`)
- Dungeons use `difficulty` (Normal/Heroic); optional `shortName` for compact display; optional `emblem` for display; legacy saves with `mode` are migrated on load; `emblem` loads only from the saved field (template rows include it in `DungeonList`; no raid-name backfill on load); missing `shortName` backfills from `RaidNames` when the name matches on load
- Characters may store optional `mainSpec` / `offSpec` (`{ spec, gearScore? }`); legacy v2 saves with flat spec strings or a single `gearScore` migrate on load (`storage/parse.ts`)
- Production `vite.config.ts` uses `manualChunks` for React / MUI vendor splits; Vitest configured in the same file (`test` block, jsdom, `src/test/setup.ts`)
- Tests: Vitest + jsdom + Testing Library; colocated `*.test.ts` / `*.test.tsx`; shared helpers in `src/test/` (`fixtures.ts`, `render-with-theme.tsx`); CI runs `npm run test:run` after lint
- App version from `package.json` via Vite `define` (`__APP_VERSION__` in `vite-env.d.ts`; label in `app-meta-info`)
- Light/dark mode: `ColorModeProvider` in `contexts/color-mode-provider.tsx` + `useColorMode`; `localStorage` key `my-raid-cds-color-mode`; pre-paint script in `index.html`; CSS vars via `:root[data-color-mode]` in `index.css`
- Sticky header: MUI `AppBar` in `app-header/` (tracker actions, theme toggle, GitHub meta)
- Follow existing patterns; check README before adding dependencies

## Key Behaviors

- **Add from template** — one-shot: loads `DungeonList` only when the dungeon list is empty; `handleAddFromTemplate` no-ops if dungeons already exist (UI hides the action; guard covers other callers)
- **Reset all toggles** — toolbar control clears all cooldown toggles (keeps characters and dungeons)
- **Delete dungeon** — per-row delete icon in the pinned actions column removes that dungeon and its toggles
- **Reset per character** — icon in the character column header clears toggles for that character only
- **Add forms** — only one of character or dungeon form open at a time; submit closes the form; duplicate character (name + class) is rejected; character form accepts optional main/off spec and gear score (WotLK specs for selected class; main and off must differ when both set); dungeon form accepts optional short name (defaults from `RaidNames` when name matches a known raid)
- **Edit character** — edit icon in character column header opens `CharacterEditDialog` to update main/off spec and gear score (name and class unchanged)
- **Character column** — shows class icon, name, optional spec icons with compact gear score (`6.6k`, rounded down); tooltip has full spec names
- **Compact table** — below `md`, pinned columns are actions + name only; name cell shows `shortName` when set (full name in tooltip)
- **Export** — filter dungeons with table search, then **Export** in toolbar; one line per visible raid lists characters without CD with optional spec short labels and compact gear scores (e.g. `Name Udk 6.6k \ Blood 6k`; see `format-character-export.ts`, `build-export-status.ts`, `format-dungeon-label.ts`)
- **Empty table** — no dungeons: body hint to add or use template; search with no matches: “No dungeons match your search” row (`raid-tracker-table-empty-state`)

## Component Structure

- **kebab-case** for component dirs (e.g. `character-form/`)
- Typical folder: `index.tsx`; add `types.ts` and/or `styles.css` when needed (not every component has all three)
- complex components like `raid-tracker-table/` may include colocated subcomponents (e.g. `dungeon-cells.tsx`, `character-header-cell.tsx`, `raid-tracker-table-head.tsx`, `dungeon-table-row.tsx`, `pinned-column-renderers.tsx`, `use-raid-tracker-table-state.ts`)
- Domain state lives in `useTrackerDomain` (persistence, toggles, deletes, template, `updateCharacter`); `RaidTrackerProvider` + `useRaidTrackerContext()` expose domain to the table and main content. `TrackerLayout` composes toolbar (`TrackerControls`), `useTrackerForms`, and export panel state; add-form field state is not in context (avoids re-rendering toolbar/table on keystrokes). Validation in `utils/validate-character.ts` and `utils/validate-dungeon.ts`. `CharacterForm` / `DungeonForm` / `CharacterEditDialog` stay presentational. `App` mounts provider + `TrackerLayout` only. Ephemeral table UI state (sort, search, pending delete, compact columns, edit-character dialog) lives in `useRaidTrackerTableState` colocated with the table. Character name display sx in `utils/character-display.ts`; spec/gear display in `utils/format-character-details.ts` and `components/spec-option-label/`.

## Project Structure

```
src/
├── components/ # app-header, tracker-layout, raid-tracker-main, character-form, character-edit-dialog, character-spec-gear-fields, spec-option-label, raid-tracker-table, tracker-controls (+ actions.ts), export-panel, …
├── constants/ # character.ts, dungeon-form-defaults.ts
├── contexts/ # raid-tracker-context.ts, raid-tracker-provider.tsx, color-mode-provider.tsx
├── hooks/ # use-tracker-domain.ts, use-compact-layout.ts, use-raid-tracker-context.ts, use-tracker-forms.ts, use-*-form-state.ts, use-export-panel-state.ts, color-mode.ts, …
├── theme/ # create-app-theme.ts
├── types/ # characters, dungeons
├── data/ # raid-names.ts, class-specs.ts, dungeon-list.ts, create-template-dungeon.ts, dungeons.ts (barrel)
├── utils/ # completion-counts, dungeon-toggles, character-display, format-character-details, format-character-export, filter/sort dungeons, validate-character/dungeon, dungeon-short-name, build-export-status, …
├── assets/ # class-icons/ (+ specs/), emblems/
├── storage/ # index.ts (public API), parse.ts, persist.ts, types, constants
├── test/ # setup.ts, fixtures.ts, render-with-theme.tsx, test-providers.tsx
├── uuid.ts # generateUUID
└── vite-env.d.ts # __APP_VERSION__ declaration
```

Colocate tests as `*.test.ts` / `*.test.tsx` beside the module under test; use `src/test/fixtures.ts` for sample characters/dungeons/toggles and `renderWithTheme` for MUI component tests.

## Communication

- Be direct and concise
- Prefer answering questions before making edits when unclear
- Explain non-obvious changes briefly
